Exercise

    For the above example modelling a falling rock:

  1. Determine whether T1 is [[2]] \(2.7\)

  2. [[5]] is a sketched graph of v for 0 ≤ t ≤ T1
    Graph A Graph B

generalfeedback.text:
1. T1 will be less thatn 2.7 since the rock will be moving faster throughout its descent.

  2. The graph is still a straight line but displaced upwards compared to the example above, therefore the y intercept is at 5. The equation of the line is v = 9.8t + 5 for the falling rock
